Miramax and Roadside Attractions partnered with The Estate of Whitney E. Houston to deliver a documentary film that goes beyond the scope of the tabloid headlines and focuses on late singer’s life. item.title: Tevin Campbell Responds To Molestation Rumor Involving Quincy Jones
item.description: Quincy Jones caused quite a stir online this week after not only spilling the tea, but dumping the entire beverage about several entertainment figures in an interview. These revelations caused many Internet users to flip the script and dig up perceived dirt on the legendary music producer. item.title: King Charles' Coronation 2023: What Time, Where to Watch
item.description: The biggest event of the year. King Charles III is set to be crowned at Westminster Abbey in London, but viewers from around the world will be able to witness the historical moment for themselves on TV. The festivities will begin bright and early on Saturday, May 6, as the ceremony will commence at 6 a.m. ET (a.k.a 11 a.m. U.K. time). CNN, NBC, Fox News and more major U.S. stations are expected to air the coronation via cable, YouTube live streams and live TV subscriptions such as Hulu + Live TV, DIRECTV, Sling TV and FuboTV.

item.title: Miley Cyrus New Man Maxx Morando: 5 Things to Know

The Disney alum, who was hosting NBC’s Miley’s New Year’s Eve Party with Pete Davidson, raised eyebrows when she debuted her new song “You.” “I got some baggage / Let’s do some damage / I am not made for no horsey and carriage / You know I’m savage / You’re looking past it / I want that late night sweet magic / That forever lasting love / But only if it’s with you,” the lyrics read, which made fans wonder if it was inspired by Morando.

item.title: Cedric Jones, Boxer And 'Emancipation' Actor, Dead At 46
item.description: Cedric “Beastie” Jones, a rising actor and founder of Beastie Boxing Gym, died on Monday, Oct. 16, at age 46. His cause of death is unknown. Jones’ death was confirmed by the boxing gym earlier this week via their Instagram and official website. “It is with a heavy heart that we announce the passing of Beastie Boxing Gym Founder, Cedric ‘Beastie’ Jones. Cedric was a loving father, devoted husband, caring son, brother, community leader, and incredible friend who inspired others,” read the statement.

item.title: Is "Marry Rich" Advocate Christine Quinn's Assault-Charged Estranged Husband Really Rich?
item.description: Highlights Despite struggles, Christine Quinn made an impact post-Selling Sunset exit, from runway walks to a self-help book. Quinn's marriage to Christian Dumontet took a dark turn, with abuse allegations leading to arrests. The reality star advocates for marrying rich, even after facing challenges with a millionaire husband’s legal troubles. Before Selling Sunset's Nicole Young became one of the most unlikeable figures on reality TV, there was self-proclaimed villain, Christine Quinn, who surprisingly left the show after season 5.

item.description: Individuals are looking for Kayla Cardona’s identity and family subtleties after she rose to conspicuousness from her part in the well known Netflix show, “Selling The OC”. This reality program fixates on the financial specialists, Jason and Bret Oppenheim, who extended their startup by opening a second office in Newport Beach. The series follows eleven realtors from the Oppenheim Group as they assist notable customer base with purchasing extravagant elegance homes in Orange County.

item.title: One Tree Hill's Bethany Joy Lenz Reveals She Was in a Cult for 10 Years
item.description: One Tree Hill alum Bethany Joy Lenz revealed she was in a cult for a decade, and she hopes that her experience can eventually help others. “I was in a cult for 10 years,” Lenz, 42, shared on the Monday, July 10, episode of iHeartRadio’s “Drama Queens” podcast. “That would be a really valuable experience to write about, and the recovery — 10 years of recovery after that. So there’s a lot to tell.

item.title: Takeoff Cause Of Death How Did He Died?
item.description: Hip hop artist Takeoff, a member of the group Migos, was tragically killed after being shot in Houston at the age of 28. During a dice game at 2 am at bowling alley 810 Billiards & Bowling, Kirshnik Khari Ball, whose real name is Kirshnik Khari Ball, got into an argument with his bandmate Quavo. It was a shootout that resulted in Takeoff’s death and the injuries of two others.

item.title: Tim Burton Hated The Original Ending To 'The Nightmare Before Christmas'
item.description: When looking through the history of animated movies, there are a few movies that stand out as ones that legitimately changed the game. Snow White was the first full-length animated movie and changed the world of film, while Toy Story was the first entirely computer-animated movie to hit theaters. In the case of The Nightmare Before Christmas, this film has been a moneymaking machine since its release, and it has inspired countless other projects.

item.title: Vin Diesel and Meadow Walkers Sweetest Moments Over the Years
item.description: Family comes first! Vin Diesel and goddaughter Meadow Walker had a close bond even before Paul Walker’s death in 2013 — and they’ve remained a tight-knit duo since his passing. Diesel formed a friendship with Paul when they both starred in 2001’s The Fast and the Furious. The men went on to play BFFs Dominic Toretto and Brian O’Conner, respectively, in four more Fast and Furious films before Paul was killed in a single-vehicle car crash at the age of 40.

item.title: Who Is Karlie Kloss Husband, Joshua Kushner?
item.description: When it comes to the world of finance, there are only a few select names that just about anyone could recognize, Kushner, being one of them. The entire family has done incredibly well for themselves, however, it was the youngest, Joshua Kushner, that had all eyes on him when he and model, Karlie Kloss tied the knot back in 2018. The Kushner family has extensive ties to the Trump family, especially after the eldest brother, Jared Kushner married Ivanka Trump.

item.title: Christina Milian, Fiance Jas Prince Split: Singer Ends Engagement
item.description: It's over. Christina Milian has called it quits with fiance Jas Prince after two years of dating, a rep for the star's family confirms exclusively to Us Weekly. The singer/songwriter/actress, 32, called off her engagement to the Rap-A-Lot Records CEO earlier this month. She moved her stuff out of their shared house in L.A. on Thursday, June 19. Milian and Prince reportedly started dating in 2010, months after her split from ex-husband The-Dream, with whom she has a 4-year-old daughter, Violet.

item.title: Depeche Mode Net Worth How Much Are Depeche Mode Worth?
item.description: Depeche Mode is a renowned English electronic band that emerged from Basildon, United Kingdom in 1980. Comprised of Dave Gahan, the lead vocalist and co-songwriter, and Martin Gore, the multi-talented musician responsible for keyboards, guitar, and co-lead vocals, as well as primary songwriting. With an estimated net worth of $180 million, Depeche Mode has made a significant mark in the music industry. Key Takeaways: Depeche Mode is an English electronic band formed in 1980.

item.title: Dominique Geisendorff Bio, Age, Family, Boyfriend, Movies and Net Worth
item.description: Dominique Geisendorff Biography Dominique Geisendorff born Dominique Nicole Geisendorff is an American celebrity star. She is best known for being involved in a long-term relationship with former Twilight star Cam Gigandet. The two got engaged in 2008. Gigandet is known for his recurring role on The O.C. and appearances in feature films like Twilight, Pandorum, Never Back Down, Burlesque, Easy A, Priest, and The Magnificent Seven. Dominique Geisendorff Age Nicole Geisendorff is 37 years old as of 2021.

item.title: Eamonn Walker Becomes Latest Cast Member to Leave Chicago Fire
item.description: Chicago Fire said goodbye to another cast mainstay in its Wednesday, May 22, season finale, with Eamonn Walker appearing in his final episode as a series regular. Walker portrays Battalion Chief Wallace Boden, who has led Firehouse 51 since the series premiered in 2012. Walker, 61, has appeared in 252 episodes over 12 seasons. He is the third series regular to leave the show this year, following Alberto Rosende and Kara Killmer, who exited in the first half of the season.

item.title: How Close Are Seth Rogen And Charlize Theron?
item.description: Celebrity friendships are always fascinating, especially when it comes to personalities that seem really juxtapositioned. Think about Martha Stewart and Snoop Dogg, for example, or Quentin Tarantino and Brad Pitt. It may not make a ton of sense on the face of it, but when fans look a little deeper, connections come in all kinds of forms. So while movie enthusiasts might not think Seth Rogen and Charlize Theron have much in common, in turns out they're closer than fans may expect.

item.title: How Robert Kardashian Stood by O.J. Simpson During his Trial
item.description: Mr. Robert Kardashian, the father of Kourtney, Kim, Khloe, and Rob Kardashian, was a well-known businessman and attorney in the United States. After his friend, O J Simpson, was acquitted and prosecuted for the murder of his ex-wife, Nicole Brown Simpson, he rose to prominence. Robert Kardashian was hired as a defense counsel in the 1995 murder case. Robert Kardashian  Born to Armenian American parents, Arthur Kardashian (1917–2012) and Helen Jean Arakelian Kardashian (1917–2008), Robert George Kardashian’s date of birth is February 22, 1944.

item.title: Is There A Reason Why Cristiano Ronaldo Hasn't Married His Long-Term GF Georgina Rodriguez?
item.description: Highlights Cristiano Ronaldo and Georgina Rodriguez have been in love since they first met in a Gucci store in 2016. Marriage is not a priority for the couple, as they believe they are already married in the eyes of God. Cristiano plans to marry Georgina in the future, but the timing is not yet set. This article was updated on November 18, 2023.

item.title: Justin Timberlake Reacts To Jessica Biel's Met Gala Look Amid Rumors Of Marriage Problems
item.description: Highlights Jessica Biel wowed at the Met Gala in stunning pink gown, while Justin Timberlake showed his appreciation on social media. Timberlake couldn't attend due to work, stirring rumors of marriage problems despite Biel's dazzling solo appearance. Despite past controversies and challenges, the couple has persevered through love, hard work, and couples therapy. While Jessica Biel wowed the crowd at this year's Met Gala, her husband, Justin Timberlake, was nowhere to be seen.

item.title: Layzie Bone Saves A Mans Life In Wyoming
item.description: Bone Thugs-N-Harmony’s Layzie Bone became an unsuspecting hero on Saturday (May 16) while driving in Riverton, WY. After witnessing a driver swerve off the road and his car do a full turn, the rapper intervened, and discovered that the man was in diabetic shock. Layzie then along with others, helped stabilize him by giving him fruit and chocolate. In an interview with local news station KTWO, the Bone Thug shrugged off the “hero” title.

item.title: Producers L&X Music Break Down J. Cole and Drakes In The Morning [Pg. 2]
item.description: THE MAKING OF THE “IN THE MORNING” BEAT: Leslie “L” Merceron: I remember the exact day we made that beat: September 13, 2007. [Laughs] The exact day. At the time, I had my production setup at my house and it was 3:30 or 4 o’clock in the morning and I couldn’t sleep. So I got up and started messing around and, funny enough, made a song that ended up being called “In The Morning.

item.title: Puma Badu Age: How Old Is She?
Quentin Tarantino, Wife Daniella Pick Welcome Their 2nd Baby
item.description: Round two! Quentin Tarantino and Daniella Pick’s second baby arrived on Saturday, July 2. “Daniella and Quentin Tarantino are happy to announce that Daniella gave birth to their baby girl on July 2, 2022, a little sister to Leo, their first child,” the pair told People on Tuesday, July 5. Us Weekly confirmed in February that the couple were expecting baby No. 2, two years after their son Leo’s birth.

item.title: Sofia Richie Seemingly Hangs Out at Scott Disicks House After Split
item.description: On the road to reconciliation? Sofia Richie seemingly caught up with ex-boyfriend Scott Disick at his house. The 21-year-old model shared an image to her Instagram Stories on Sunday, July 12, of herself watching Netflix’s Down to Earth With Zac Efron. The location from which she tuned into the newly released series resembles the living room of Disick’s Hidden Hills home, which he re-listed in April. Richie’s apparent hang out with the 37-year-old Talentless cofounder comes after the duo reunited over the 4th of July.

item.title: What Sarah Jessica Parker Really Thought About 'The Carrie Diaries'
item.description: The upcoming Sex and the City sequel, And Just Like That is rejected by many fans of the show. With Kim Cattrall, 65, not reprising her role as the sex goddess, Samantha Jones, they think there isn't much to see anymore except the old toxic relationship of Carrie Bradshaw and Big (played by Sarah Jessica Parker, 56, and Chris Noth, 66). Some even say that the HBO Max mini-series might be a flop like the second SATC movie.

item.title: 19-Year-Old University of Kentucky Pre-Med Student Drowns In Isreal
item.description: Authorities in Tel Aviv, Israel found the body of University of Kentucky pre-med student TeNiya Elnora Jones on a beach on Monday (Jul 20), New Press reports. The 19-year-old was reportedly accompanied by two other students who all went of a midnight swim on Sunday night (Jul 29). The two students survived a huge current that swallowed them into the ocean but Jones drowned. Before the accident happened, Jones’ mother Tosha Thomas-Mora was reportedly in contact with her that night (10:30 pm Israeli time; 3:330 pm EST American time) via text message, where Jones said she was “in for the night.

item.title: A$AP Rocky Found Guilty Of Assault In Sweden
item.description: A$AP Rocky has been convicted of assault and given a suspended sentence for the altercation that took place in Stockholm, Sweden on June 30. According to CNN, the artist and two members of his entourage (David Rispers and Bladimir Corniel) were given the same verdict on Wednesday (Aug. 14) after a week of deliberations. Despite claims and video evidence of self-defense from the rapper and his crew, the court found Rocky, born Rakim Mayers, liable of assault against 19-year-old Mustafa Jafari.

item.title: How Much Was Beth Ostrosky Worth Before Marrying Howard Stern
item.description: Howard Stern married his wife Beth Ostrosky at Le Cirque restaurant in New York City in October 2008 and 13 years later the couple is still going strong. They met in 2000 at a mutual friends’ party and hit it off so well they started dating soon after. Howard has had tremendous success over the years and despite beingrumoured to be a secret billionaire, he has a net worth of $650 million.

item.title: How old was Ned Dubofsky? Everything to know about Camp Winaukee as member dies unexpectedly
item.description: Ned Dubofsky, a graduate of Camp Winaukee, apparently died on Thursday, February 9, 2023. He was 54 years of age at the hour of his destruction. The insight about his passing was declared in a post on the Winaukee 100 Facebook bunch, which was set up to praise the 100th commemoration of Camp Winaukee. Ned Dubofsky supposedly lost his life in a mishap.
